ibm2212AdapTable.name: ibm2212AdapTable
ibm2212AdapTable.description: A table of information about adapters in this box.

ibm2212AdapEntry.name: ibm2212AdapEntry
ibm2212AdapEntry.description: An entry containing objects to describe the adapter in a given slot.

ibm2212AdapSlotNum.name: ibm2212AdapSlotNum
ibm2212AdapSlotNum.description: The number identifying a slot location where an adapter can be inserted. The 2212 has four fixed serial ports on the system card that are designated by slot 0.

ibm2212AdapType.name: ibm2212AdapType
ibm2212AdapType.description: The type of adapter that is inserted into this slot. Not all of the adapter types listed above are necessarily currently available and supported. The four fixed serial ports on the system card are identified by the serial-4port-shallow(7) enumeration. If no adapter is present, the variable will take the value not-present(2).

ibm2212AdapOperStatus.name: ibm2212AdapOperStatus
ibm2212AdapOperStatus.description: The operational status of this adapter. unknown (1) : If there was problem determining the operational status of the adapter. not-present (2) : If no adapter is currently inserted. enable-pending (3) : Adapter has been identified, but not yet enabled. enabled (4) : Adapter has been identified in valid slot and has been powered on and enabled. unknown-device (5) : Adapter is powered off because it is in the wrong slot or of unknown type. config-error (6) : Adapter has been identified, powered on and enabled, but failed to read its configuration data. not-powered (7) : Adapter has been identified in valid slot but is not currently powered on.

ibm2212GraphicTable.name: ibm2212GraphicTable
ibm2212GraphicTable.description: A table of information mapping a slot and port to an interface table ifIndex. An entry exists in this table only if the ifConnectorPresent object is true

ibm2212GraphicEntry.name: ibm2212GraphicEntry
ibm2212GraphicEntry.description: An entry mapping slot and port to an interface table ifIndex.

ibm2212GraphicSlotNum.name: ibm2212GraphicSlotNum
ibm2212GraphicSlotNum.description: The number identifying a slot location where an adapter can be inserted. The 2212 has four fixed serial ports on the system card that are designated by slot 0.

ibm2212GraphicPortNum.name: ibm2212GraphicPortNum
ibm2212GraphicPortNum.description: The number identifying a port on a given adapter. A port implies a physical connector is associated with it.

ibm2212GraphicifIndex.name: ibm2212GraphicifIndex
ibm2212GraphicifIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface table entry associated with this port on an adapter. By definition, the ifEntry has ifConnectorPresent = true.
